Job Description:
The Global market for robot assisted minimal access surgery is projected to increase at a CAGR of 13%; is expected to grow to $17.9 billion by 2020. We have just completed a significant Series A funding round and are looking for talents who share our vision and dedication to join us for this exciting venture. If you are interested in any of the jobs listed below, please write to: info@precisionrobotics.com, along with a cover letter, your detailed CV, and other supporting materials.
Precision Robotics is the home for next generation surgical robots, developing new technologies that support the future of precision surgery for personalised healthcare and quality of life improvements. The company is addressing the high demand for modern robotic surgery methods through unique platforms, which combine a range of patented technologies to deliver advantages to surgeons and patients. The first product incorporates fully articulated robotic arms, which provide accurate manoeuvres and a high level of control to surgeons, and a unique 3-D Augmented Reality-based image navigation software. Headquartered in London, the company also has offices in Hong Kong, bringing together talents in both engineering development and clinical translation. We are looking a skilled Software Engineer to join our team for a 6 month contract in January 2020.

Requirements:
2+ year experience in software engineering, algorithm implementation
Bachelor's degree in computer science, computing, electronics and related.
Expert in C++ programming in Linux
Experience on robotics and real-time communication is a bonus
Job Duty:
Writing software programming for Precision Robotics products;
Liaise with hardware and high-level software engineers to ensure seamless integration;
Develop, review, test, debug software to ensure correct functionalities;
Analysis and improvement on software efficiency;
Support software QA for the company products;
Provide documentation for certification;
Provide related documentation for regulatory and certification requirements
Perform other activities as required by the Company and ensure the activities are conducted in line with regulatory and the company's requirements.
