Elephant is a tech startup tackling the big problems in global healthcare. We create lightweight, connectable applications that improve access to care and save lives. We work in emerging economies and have partnered with NGOs, Governments, and healthcare professionals around the world.

In 2020 our platform is expanding and will reach more than 2 million new patients in Africa and the Middle East.

We are looking for a talented junior full stack engineer who can bring imagination, enthusiasm and passion to our ambitious projects.

A short video providing more information about our Kenyan operations can be found here: https://vimeo.com/369570618/a5d3d8f82f.

What sort of company are we?

We are a small band of experts. We are focused on delivering solutions to frontline professionals. Our culture is open, creative and collaborative, and we believe that products, whether used in Sudan or San Francisco should be intuitive and beautiful.

We have a culture based on security, kindness, candour, and good humour. If you think you have what it takes, please get in touch.

The role

We are looking for intermediate to senior level software developers to join our expanding development team.

Intermediate members of the team have access to exceptional senior experience across the full stack for guidance, and will be strongly encouraged to develop your their technical capabilities through self-driven learning and development.

Senior members of the team will have leadership responsibilities and ability to influence the direction of the engineering team.
Be part of a dynamic and growing engineering team specialising in creating an exceptional product firmly grounded in principles of data science and analytics.
You will be an integral part of a small and capable engineering team focused on creating exceptional products being used in some of the world’s most extreme environments.
The scope of your work includes leading and/or contributing to team sprints, assisting with technical debt, roadmapping and architecture solutions.
You will work closely with other engineers, product managers, data scientists, and designers.
We value the expertise and voice of every team member, and you will be pivotal in shaping the future of our engineering team’s culture and technical stack.
Requirements

What skills and experience would we like you to have?

Essential skills:
At least 2+ years experience working with a programming language building web/mobile apps or API services using Javascript or Python (ES or TS a bonus);
Good understanding of React. We are open to those with experience of Vue, Angular or Ember who are willing to move to React;
Experience with CSS and a templating engine (JSX great);
An appreciation of clean code and good design principles;
An understanding of algorithms and data structure;
Working with RESTful API endpoints using libraries such as Axios for request/response and parsing;
A good understanding of unit and integration testing (e.g. using Jest);
Experience with Git for version control;
An appreciation/understanding of state management in UI applications (we use Redux and RxJs);
An appreciation of working with service-based architecture (sync/async comms, CQRS etc...)
An understanding of unit, integration and acceptance testing;
Experience of, or working with relational/non-relational databases (MongoDB a plus);
Knowledge of cloud-based systems - AWS a plus;
Understanding of operating systems (Linux);
Excellent communication and organisational skills; and
Appreciation of agile methodologies, respect for testing and safe code.
Desired:
Experience building mobile apps;
Working with front-end performance problems;
Experience of writing front-end acceptance tests using Puppeteer and the headless Chrome API;
Experience of webpack;
Experience working on secure products that handle sensitive data is a major plus, e.g. Healthcare or FinTech; and
Direct experience working with ML in production.
Benefits

What do we pay and what are our benefits?

The starting pay is £45,000 pa + dependant on experience, with generous stock options for intermediate engineers. Senior engineers can expect salaries of £75,000 pa + share options dependant on experience.

Your salary and benefits will grow significantly as the company continues to grow.

We are currently working remote due to Coronavirus and hope to be able to continue to offer flexible working arrangements as we move back into an office space in central London.

Our benefits include:
Employee pension scheme with Aviva.
25 days holidays + public holidays.
We also offer the opportunity for international travel to engage with our customers on the frontline.
